Dialogue: 0,0:00:09.25,0:00:11.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}In order to protect the\Npurity of the 4.5 tatami room,{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:11.91,0:00:13.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I don iron armor when venturing outside.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:13.83,0:00:17.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Armed by theory, sophistries at the ready,\Nwith a brazen, soft-coated, nonchalant smile,{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:18.75,0:00:23.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I give no mercy to wretched souls running wild.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:25.37,0:00:26.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}However, the more I defeat,{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:26.33,0:00:28.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}the more this indescribable \Nloneliness presses down upon me.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:28.38,0:00:29.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Why? {\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:29.20,0:00:31.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Wasn't this a holy war\Nfought on the side of justice?{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:34.38,0:00:35.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Now, with all humanity gone... {\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:35.83,0:00:38.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}With my studies, exercise,\Npopularity, good looks, all left behind...{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:38.91,0:00:42.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I lie here, completely removed\Nfrom those crucial pillars, stark naked.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:42.39,0:00:44.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I wish I could go back in time to that day!{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:20.75,0:02:23.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}In the beginning of the Paleozoic era,\Nthe Cambrian explosion occurred,{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:23.12,0:02:25.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}and a large number of\Norganisms made their appearance.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:25.20,0:02:26.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Then, at the end of the Paleozoic era,{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:26.66,0:02:27.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}the world changed {\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:27.25,0:02:28.16,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,2 Tatami Age (Permian Period)
Dialogue: 0,0:02:27.70,0:02:28.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}to an infinite spread of 2 tatami,{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:28.78,0:02:32.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}and in the beginning of the Mesozoic era it\Nincreased by one as the "3 Tatami Age" arrived.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:32.38,0:02:34.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}But as the dinosaurs appeared, {\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:34.37,0:02:36.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}the laid out tatami were\Ncompletely stomped into nothingness,{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:36.58,0:02:38.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}and time moved on to the Jurassic Period.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:38.95,0:02:39.83,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,Cretaceous Period
Dialogue: 0,0:02:39.83,0:02:41.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}After that came the majestic glory of humanity.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:40.45,0:02:41.83,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,Tertiary Period
Dialogue: 0,0:02:41.83,0:02:42.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}And before long, in the present world,{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:42.45,0:02:43.50,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,Quaternary Period
Dialogue: 0,0:02:42.97,0:02:43.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}as the bell tolls for the end of{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:43.87,0:02:44.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}the quaternary part of the Cenozoic period,{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:44.94,0:02:46.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}once again tatami have been\Nspread out across the world,{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:46.56,0:02:48.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}marking the beginning of the "4.5 Tatami Age."{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:50.81,0:02:53.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Going back in time is quite unbelievable.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:53.12,0:02:54.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}However, I was wandering, lost, {\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:54.58,0:02:58.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}in an unbelievable world of infinitely\Nmany 4.5 tatami rooms laid side by side.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:59.44,0:03:01.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}It had already been 2 months\Nsince I began wandering.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:01.03,0:03:05.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Even though I figured this world had no end,\NI continued my pitiful, endless march.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:07.04,0:03:08.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}"If I open the door, there is the hallway."{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:08.54,0:03:11.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}That would be an astronomical,\Nmiraculous, and fortuitous happening.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:11.54,0:03:14.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}All the rooms looked the same,\Nbut they all had slight differences.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:14.37,0:03:16.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Each one was inhabited\Nby a slightly different me.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:17.42,0:03:21.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}However, all of them seemed to have\Nled some gloriously wasted campus life.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:22.05,0:03:26.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I tried to begin studying\Neach one, and myself as a whole,{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:26.12,0:03:27.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}but I immediately lost my motivation,{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:27.37,0:03:28.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}and instead my interest shifted {\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:28.87,0:03:33.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}to the traces in each room of the\Nvarious people I was mixed up with.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:33.36,0:03:36.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}The person named Aijima was one year older\Nthan me and the head of the Library Committee.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:36.04,0:03:38.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}He was a small man who would not allow\Nyou to check out more than 2 books at once,{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:38.54,0:03:40.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}but you could see in his eyes through those\Nglasses that his polite face masked hypocrisy,{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:40.50,0:03:42.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}and I got an impression\Nthat he was insufferable.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:42.20,0:03:45.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I recall seeing something of a purge in\Nsome Secret Society he was in charge of{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:45.55,0:03:48.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}after someone entrapped him. {\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:50.08,0:03:52.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Now that I think about it, earlier...{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:54.48,0:03:57.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Do you know a Higuchi\Nwho lives on the second floor?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:57.29,0:03:58.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:58.54,0:04:02.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I see. We are collecting\Ninformation on this man.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:03.56,0:04:06.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This guy has caused everyone\Nquite a lot of trouble, see...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:06.58,0:04:10.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He's like some {\i1}youkai {\i0}with\Nno redeemable aspect at all.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:10.49,0:04:12.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}The two that came calling\Nhad their faces covered,{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:12.54,0:04:15.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}but that vocal tick had to have been Aijima.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:15.45,0:04:19.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Then I'm going to tell you a number of things.\NIf anything comes to mind, answer.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:19.37,0:04:24.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Airship. Gozan. Honwaka. Kohinata.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:26.19,0:04:29.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Kohinata-san was the poster child\Nof a raven-haired maiden on campus.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:29.50,0:04:30.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}If I were ever perchance to meet her,{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:30.70,0:04:32.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I bet I would lavish her with\Ngifts without a second thought,{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:32.91,0:04:35.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}regardless of the hardship on myself.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:36.28,0:04:40.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}With their word association game\Nnot bearing any fruit, the two left.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:40.68,0:04:44.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}That dental hygienist Hanuki-san\Nwas also an alumni of my university.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:44.20,0:04:47.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}And I knew that the two of\Nthem were in the same year.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:47.26,0:04:50.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}While I'm mentioning it, that cart owner\Nalso seems to be from the same year.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:50.01,0:04:51.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}It's a small world, you know? {\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:52.52,0:04:54.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Mr. Higuchi was an eighth\Nyear student on the brink,{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:54.62,0:04:57.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}but he was fixed in his ways and took things at\Nhis own pace, although he had a stately manner.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:58.36,0:05:00.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Hanuki-san would frequently\Nvisit him at the boarding house,{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:00.77,0:05:02.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}and it seems like he took\Non a couple of apprentices.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:03.16,0:05:04.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Why was he so revered? {\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:04.78,0:05:07.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}His extremely useless life,\Nhis propensity for fierce self-effacement.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:07.66,0:05:09.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Perhaps it was all lined with deep learning.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:12.03,0:05:14.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}In one of my lives, I had become his disciple.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:15.66,0:05:17.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}The man whose entire body seemed\Nchiseled out of stone, Mr. Jougasaki,{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:17.79,0:05:21.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}seemed to have taken over some\Nwar of pranks with Mr. Higuchi.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:21.45,0:05:23.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}He didn't look like that sort of person at all,{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:23.20,0:05:26.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}but he succeeded as the\Nnext proxy, or something.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:29.26,0:05:31.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}While Mr. Jougasaki had a lover named Kaori-san,{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:31.58,0:05:33.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}he seemed to have some interest in Hanuki-san.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:33.24,0:05:36.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Hanuki-san seemed to be both be\Ndating Mr. Higuchi and not dating him,{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:36.41,0:05:39.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}and anyway Mr. Higuchi said that he\Nwas going on a trip around the world.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:39.36,0:05:41.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Will you come with me, Hanuki? {\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:41.12,0:05:43.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}You can speak English, right? {\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:43.45,0:05:45.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Don't be crazy. This is foolishness.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:45.86,0:05:48.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Mr. Higuchi had feelings for Hanuki-san,{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:48.00,0:05:50.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}and yet he was going to leave her...\NHow frustrating.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:50.52,0:05:54.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Perhaps it was like he was pretending not to\Nnotice the diamond dropped on the roadside?{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:55.72,0:05:59.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Looking at it like this, humans\Nreally are deep; they have many faces.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:59.12,0:06:02.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}It's a huge shame to scorn people just\Nbecause of a single hasty look at the surface.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:02.66,0:06:05.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}If you look at them from all angles,\Nyou'll be able to see new, hidden sides to them.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:06.17,0:06:08.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I will put everything that\NI've been up on this shelf,{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:08.75,0:06:11.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}and once having put it all aside,\NI won't dare to take it down again.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:11.14,0:06:14.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}However, I should have been\Nsatisfied to the point of bursting{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:14.14,0:06:16.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}by all these different people\Nsurrounding my campus lives.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:16.58,0:06:18.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}What in the world was I doing? {\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:18.28,0:06:20.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I knew not how to partake of the world.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:18.89,0:06:21.08,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,Castella
Dialogue: 0,0:06:18.89,0:06:21.08,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,Fishburger
Dialogue: 0,0:06:18.89,0:06:21.08,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,Other
Dialogue: 0,0:06:18.89,0:06:21.08,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,Me
Dialogue: 0,0:06:21.65,0:06:23.40,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,I want to eat rice
Dialogue: 0,0:06:23.40,0:06:24.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}A convenience store onigiri would do.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:24.91,0:06:26.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Even if it was cold and hardened...{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:26.45,0:06:29.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I'd trade 1000 fishburgers for 1 onigiri!{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:29.20,0:06:31.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}If a bowl of fresh cooked\Nrice were placed before me,{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:31.95,0:06:34.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I am sure tears would flood\Ndown from my eyes in torrents!{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:34.41,0:06:36.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}But what I truly yearn for is Neko Ramen...{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:36.41,0:06:37.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}A world where I can go eat at Neko Ramen,{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:37.79,0:06:39.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}setting up shop randomly\Nin the middle of the night...{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:39.42,0:06:40.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}That world is what I'd call... {\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:40.12,0:06:41.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}...paradise.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:43.33,0:06:44.38,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,Ozu
Dialogue: 0,0:06:45.05,0:06:47.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}The person who brought a\Ncastella to most of my rooms.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:47.88,0:06:51.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Participating in many circles,\NI still don't have a full portrait of him.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:51.79,0:06:53.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}From the info I have, he would\Nget in the way of people's love,{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:53.54,0:06:56.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}setting off fires and scenes\Nof carnage on a daily basis.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:56.75,0:06:59.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}As the disciple of Master Higuchi he\Ncreated an exposé film on Mr. Jougasaki,{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:59.72,0:07:01.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}all the while sucking up to Mr. Jougasaki,{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:01.40,0:07:04.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}and as a double agent\Ndyeing Mr. Higuchi's yukata pink.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:04.90,0:07:08.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Before long as a tool of Aijima he\Nwas kicked out of the movie circle,{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:08.45,0:07:11.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}and this time entrapping Aijima, he climbed\Nhis way to the top of the Secret Society.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:11.70,0:07:14.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}That bulletin board was also Ozu's doing!{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:14.54,0:07:18.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}While extolling the joys of the\NRenaissance man-like campus life,{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:18.16,0:07:20.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}he continued to meddle in every one of my lives.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:20.16,0:07:24.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}If I had only met him, then I bet my\Ncampus life would have been a fun one.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:24.04,0:07:27.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Ozu always seemed to be my only real friend.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:49.42,0:07:52.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}This was Ozu's smart phone\Nthat he must have forgotten.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:52.41,0:07:57.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I tried all kinds of passwords, then for fun\NI punched in Kohinata-san's name and it unlocked.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:57.20,0:07:59.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Amazingly, it seems that\NKohinata-san was Ozu's girlfriend!{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:59.91,0:08:00.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I couldn't believe it. {\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:00.87,0:08:03.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Why didn't he ever introduce her to me?{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:04.19,0:08:06.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}But it seemed like this was Ozu's big secret.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:07.53,0:08:11.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Ozu asked to borrow the airship\Nthat Honwaka had, but he was told no.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:12.04,0:08:14.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,They were tossed around in the\Ncrowd of people, and she ended up crying.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:14.87,0:08:18.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,W-Wait, I can't just... So suddenly...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:18.06,0:08:21.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}The ceremonial fires of Gozan are a\Nsymbol of the summer nights of Kyoto.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:21.87,0:08:23.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}On the five mountains surrounding the basin,{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:23.47,0:08:28.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}"Daimonji," "Myouho," "The Ship," the left\N"Daimonji," and "The Gate" are each lit up in order.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:28.07,0:08:31.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}It is impossible to see them\Nall from the ground at once.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:31.16,0:08:35.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}But Ozu planned on going on a sightseeing\Nflight to see the Gozan with Kohinata-san.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:35.07,0:08:36.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Is he an idiot? {\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:37.91,0:08:40.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}It seemed like Ozu planned\Non taking the airship by force.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:40.91,0:08:42.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I'm just borrowing it. {\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:43.18,0:08:46.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}What a fearfully pure love.\NAn idiot through and through.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:46.17,0:08:48.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I wonder where he gets all that boldness from?{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:48.75,0:08:50.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Is this really the judgment of {\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:50.33,0:08:52.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}a human whose heart is so twisted\Nthey are mistaken for a youkai?{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:53.88,0:08:56.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We're collecting information on this man.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:56.92,0:09:01.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Gozan. Airship. Kohinata.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:01.00,0:09:04.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}He's heading right into Aijima's clutches!{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:04.06,0:09:07.66,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,Aijima knows about your plan!\NWatch out! Gozan isn't
Dialogue: 0,0:09:07.66,0:09:10.07,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,Please charge
Dialogue: 0,0:09:15.24,0:09:18.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Gozan was more than 2 months\Nafter the day I became lost in this world.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:23.87,0:09:25.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}If I could escape from here, {\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:25.41,0:09:28.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I'd eat the tarako spaghetti at\NCafé Collection, I'd slurp Neko Ramen,{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:28.79,0:09:31.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I'd dive into the large tub at the public bath,{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:31.13,0:09:32.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I'd go see movies at Kawaramachi,{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:32.50,0:09:34.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I'd haggle with the old\Nbookstore owner on Gabino,{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:34.01,0:09:35.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I'd even listen during lectures at school!{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:35.91,0:09:38.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I'd become Master Higuchi's\Ndisciple and engage in lewd storytelling,{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:38.51,0:09:40.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I'd experience Hanuki-san's\Nendless night of hell,{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:40.54,0:09:43.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I'd help Mr. Jougasaki with\Nhis passionate, meaningless films,{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:43.02,0:09:45.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I'd even try dabbling in the secret society.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:49.87,0:09:53.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Though I tried lying to myself as consolation,\Nit became harder and harder every day.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:56.90,0:09:58.91,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,yrotavaL
Dialogue: 0,0:10:05.75,0:10:08.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}This is the room I originally lived in.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:08.29,0:10:09.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Somehow, after these\Nhow many tens of days,{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:09.70,0:10:12.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I had returned to the\N4.5 tatami room I started at.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:12.54,0:10:15.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Could it be that the corner of an\Nendless world of 4.5 tatami rooms{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:15.34,0:10:18.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I believed so strongly I was traveling\Nthrough was in fact a small loop?{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:18.70,0:10:21.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Is this the end of the world? Am I dead?{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:21.04,0:10:23.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I wish I could live happily\Ntogether with everyone...{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:24.28,0:10:27.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I had thought the days were all wasted,\Nbut they were such a bounty!{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:27.73,0:10:31.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Always dreaming of the unrealistic,\NI never looked at what I had right around me.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:31.08,0:10:34.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}That was the life I chose.\NAnd this is the result I wished for.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:39.41,0:10:43.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}It was early evening at the Shimogamo\Nused book fair the previous summer.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:43.33,0:10:45.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Only a short stretch from my boarding house,{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:45.74,0:10:48.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I would go there every day, fishing for books.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:12.40,0:11:14.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What are those?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:15.24,0:11:16.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Each one is a "Mochiguma."
Dialogue: 0,0:11:16.82,0:11:21.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,All five as a group are called the\N"Mochiguman," but I have lost one of them.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:22.16,0:11:23.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}At that point her expression, {\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:23.45,0:11:27.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}which was like some European\Nfortress city, relaxed into a smile,{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:27.25,0:11:29.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}and that smile made an impression\Nthat has never left my mind.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:30.57,0:11:35.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}In short, frankly, to put it plainly,\Nhonestly, saying it without any reservation,{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:35.41,0:11:36.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}at that moment... {\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:37.85,0:11:39.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I fell head over heels for her. {\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:41.95,0:11:45.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}That night, when I went to collect my\Nclothes from the laundromat, mysteriously,{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:45.33,0:11:48.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}my charcoal-colored boxers\NI had lovingly worn the past two years{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:48.75,0:11:51.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}had been switched with\Nthis little stuffed fellow.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:51.98,0:11:55.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}And although I put it in my\Npocket intending to give it to her...{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:56.48,0:12:00.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I should have thought to look for her,\Nbut I never took the first step.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:01.92,0:12:06.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Stop wandering aimlessly, and grab\Nthat opportunity with all your heart!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:08.49,0:12:12.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I'll take that step now...\NWhether it takes 100 steps, or 1000!{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:48.83,0:13:49.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Ozu-{\i1}kun{\i0}?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:51.20,0:13:53.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Ozu, have you no shame?!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:53.31,0:13:55.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You damn traitor!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:55.31,0:13:57.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You've got nowhere to run, Ozu!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:57.73,0:14:00.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Ozu{\i1}-senpai, {\i0}have you done some more mischief?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:01.16,0:14:04.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If you say you're gonna do\Nsomething to me, then I'm jumping!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:04.45,0:14:07.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm not coming down until\Nyou can guarantee my safety!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:07.70,0:14:11.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You think you're in a position\Nto bargain for your safety?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:11.16,0:14:12.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:12.62,0:14:14.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Think about what you've done!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:14.87,0:14:17.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Enough! I'm jumping!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:17.37,0:14:19.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm gonna jump!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:46.62,0:14:50.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Ozu!!!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:58.54,0:15:02.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Ozu! Ozu! Ozu!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:02.91,0:15:04.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Ozu!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:35.70,0:15:37.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Who are you?!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:37.12,0:15:39.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's me, Ozu!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:39.04,0:15:40.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You're naked?!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:40.75,0:15:43.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Leave this to me! I'll cover for you!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:43.38,0:15:45.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:48.76,0:15:50.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Moths?!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:59.04,0:16:01.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}It was in the Kyoto newspaper the next day,{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:01.62,0:16:05.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}but the sudden outbreak of moths\Nis still not properly understood.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:05.04,0:16:07.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}However, I suspect you\Ndear viewers understand.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:07.79,0:16:09.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He actually fell!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:09.83,0:16:10.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Crap!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:10.53,0:16:11.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Save him!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:11.37,0:16:12.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,How about we kill him instead?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:12.51,0:16:14.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He's the type of guy who wouldn't\Nstay down even if you killed him!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:14.53,0:16:16.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Ow, ow, ow! My leg is broken!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:16.87,0:16:18.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Please, let me go!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:18.45,0:16:20.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm not letting you go, no matter what!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:20.33,0:16:22.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Why do you care about me?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:22.50,0:16:25.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You and I are connected\Nby the black thread of fate!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:25.54,0:16:26.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I don't know what you're talking about!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:26.91,0:16:27.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And I don't like it!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:29.92,0:16:32.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Ozu is not going to run away, so calm down!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:32.54,0:16:34.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I will take responsibility.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:34.18,0:16:36.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Master, you're so cool!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:38.22,0:16:39.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I ended up falling...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:39.75,0:16:45.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,When I said to "break a leg"\Nfor a girl, I didn't mean for real.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:45.04,0:16:47.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You're one incorrigible fool, you know.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:47.33,0:16:48.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Why, thank you!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:49.25,0:16:51.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You reap what you sow, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:51.19,0:16:53.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What nerve you've got.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:53.04,0:16:55.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm sorry, Jougasaki-{\i1}san{\i0}.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:55.20,0:16:57.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Leave him to me.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:00.45,0:17:04.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Aren't you also a resident\Nof Shimogamo Yuusuisou?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:04.16,0:17:05.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:05.75,0:17:07.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'll leave Ozu to you.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:07.96,0:17:10.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Cover yourself with this.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:11.76,0:17:13.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You can't go by yourself!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:13.58,0:17:15.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hanuki-{\i1}san{\i0} is waiting for you!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:15.54,0:17:16.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I know that.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:16.55,0:17:17.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:17.75,0:17:20.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Show her you're a man! Tell her "Come with me!"
Dialogue: 0,0:17:20.93,0:17:23.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You're an interesting person, aren't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:25.08,0:17:26.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Having failed to steal the airship,{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:17:26.54,0:17:28.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}he changed into women's clothes\Nat the suggestion of Master Higuchi{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:17:28.91,0:17:30.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}and returned to Shimogamo\Ndown the canals of Lake Biwa{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:17:30.75,0:17:32.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}where he was supposed to\Nrendezvous with the Master...{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:17:32.30,0:17:34.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}But the disguise was easily seen through,\Nor rather made him stand out more.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:17:34.90,0:17:37.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}And he was cornered by Honwaka, and\Nmembers of the Lucky Cat Chinese Restaurant,{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:17:37.10,0:17:39.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}plus Mr. Jougasaki who had\Nrealized the betrayal of his disciple,{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:17:39.12,0:17:41.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}plus all manner of people whose\Nlove he had gotten in the way of,{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:17:41.91,0:17:45.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}until he was forced onto the railing\Nof the Kamo-oohashi and fell off.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:17:57.54,0:17:58.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What's this?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:58.47,0:17:59.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's something I once picked up.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:59.95,0:18:01.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I believe it is yours, correct?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:01.72,0:18:04.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Could you be the owner\Nof the mouse-colored boxers?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:05.16,0:18:10.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A year ago when I washed the Mochiguma,\Nthey got switched with some men's underwear.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:11.02,0:18:13.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And I've been searching\Nfor their owner ever since!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:13.95,0:18:16.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I think that underwear will fit me perfectly!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:18.96,0:18:20.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So, if you'd like...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:20.70,0:18:22.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,How about we go to Neko Ramen?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:22.66,0:18:23.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Sure!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:24.19,0:18:27.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,For some reason I have a feeling like I've\Nbeen waiting for those words for a long time.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:31.41,0:18:33.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Is it really that delicious?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:33.92,0:18:35.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, that's nice.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:35.58,0:18:37.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This flavor really is unmatched.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:38.50,0:18:40.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Because it is not the purpose of this program{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:40.37,0:18:42.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}to show the further development\Nof my relationship with Akashi-san,{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:42.95,0:18:44.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I will refrain from showing much.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:44.95,0:18:48.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I wouldn't want to throw my dear viewers'\Ntime down the gutter, now would I?{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:48.18,0:18:51.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Nothing else is as boring to\Ntell as a story of successful love.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:56.19,0:18:59.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I was half forced to become\NMaster Higuchi's disciple,{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:59.62,0:19:02.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}and the Master has now disappeared\Non his journey around the world.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:08.71,0:19:10.25,On Top,,0000,0000,0000,,{\a6}Do not try this with normal scrub brush
Dialogue: 0,0:19:10.78,0:19:14.71,OS,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}My regret at becoming his disciple\Nwas some of the fastest in history,{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:14.71,0:19:16.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}but as I pulled the pins out from the globe,{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:16.41,0:19:19.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I became entranced imagining\Nwhere Master Higuchi must be now.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:20.97,0:19:24.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Mr. Jougasaki said he left the laboratory\Nand planned to get a job somewhere.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:24.33,0:19:27.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Speaking of which, I wonder where\Nthe wordless beauty "Kaori-san" is now?{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:27.08,0:19:31.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I pray that Mr. Jougasaki and she are\Nleading a happy life together somewhere.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:31.23,0:19:33.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}The one thing Master Higuchi worried about,{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:33.16,0:19:36.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}the "Masochistic Proxy-Proxy War,"\Nwas carried on by Ozu and myself.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:36.16,0:19:41.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}While he was in the hospital, I painted\Nthe bicycle he called "Dark Scorpion" pink.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:42.75,0:19:45.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}To go along with the great change in myself,{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:45.00,0:19:48.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I found a new boarding house in\NMototanaka, and moved there with all haste.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:48.45,0:19:51.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}After all, I never wanted to spend the\Nnight in that 4.5 tatami room ever again.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:51.50,0:19:54.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}This time I chose a 6 tatami room\Nand made sure it had its own bathroom.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:02.26,0:20:03.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Ozu-{\i1}san{\i0} has a girlfriend?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:04.36,0:20:06.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, I can't let that one go by.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:06.16,0:20:10.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He stole the airship in order to\Nlet her see the bonfires from the air.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:10.54,0:20:12.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, is that why?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:12.08,0:20:15.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He even called you all to the\NKamo-oohashi to show how gallant he was.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:15.16,0:20:17.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I see. But he failed, didn't he?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:17.95,0:20:21.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Ozu-{\i1}san {\i0}really hates it when\Nthe conversation turns to love.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:21.75,0:20:24.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Perhaps he turns into a good boy\Nwhen he's in front of his girlfriend.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:27.33,0:20:29.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, the gang's all here.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:29.62,0:20:34.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Even with all that evil you did, you still\Nhad time to go out with Kohinata-{\i1}san{\i0}, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:35.75,0:20:37.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,W-What might you be talking about?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:37.46,0:20:40.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I heard that you once\Ncalled Hanuki-{\i1}san {\i0}for advice
Dialogue: 0,0:20:40.00,0:20:43.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,when you thought you were\Nbeing dumped, isn't that right?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:45.22,0:20:46.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Lies! It's all lies!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:46.58,0:20:47.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Tell us all about it!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:47.75,0:20:50.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I invoke my right to\Nremain silent! I want a lawyer!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:53.95,0:20:56.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You have a tough time even\Nwhile you're in the hospital, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:56.45,0:20:57.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I don't want to hear that from you.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:58.19,0:21:00.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Then why don't you run away\Nsomewhere until things cool down?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:00.83,0:21:02.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Leave the expenses to me!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:02.37,0:21:05.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What are you plotting? You can't fool me!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:05.24,0:21:08.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You should try trusting in other people more.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:08.20,0:21:12.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,There are big-hearted people\Nlike me in this world, you know.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:12.29,0:21:15.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,In exchange, let me meet your girlfriend!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:15.00,0:21:17.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No way! I refuse! You're so evil!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:17.46,0:21:19.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Fine then! It's all for your sake!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:21.12,0:21:24.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Why must you be so interested in me?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:24.05,0:21:26.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's the way I show my love.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:26.05,0:21:28.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You can keep that icky love to yourself!
